commitResults.messageTitle: Level 1: Bot greets user, echos input and says bye to user if input is bye
Level 1: Fixed minor bug. Should not echo if input is bye
Level 1: Made fields and methods in class Pixel private
Level 2: Created list, added the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
Level 3: Add the ability to mark tasks as done. Optionally, add the ability to change the status back to not done.
Level 4: Correctly implemented todo, event and deadline
A-TextUiTesting: Fixed minor bug, label display for Deadline, ToDo and Event (D/T/E)

A-TextUiTesting: Finalised tests, fixed the bug where command text (todo/ event/ deadline) is wrongly displayed along with the actual message. Also accounted for the case where the user does not set a due date by using /

Level-6: Switched from array to ArrayList to store the Tasks. Also implemented deletion of tasks. But code is still quite buggy. Also level of abstraction of code is too low and needs to be further refined.
Level-5.1: Created custom exception for incorrect format of input (not a task or command)

Level-5.2: Created greater abstraction of the methods when handling the different types of tasks. No longer accepts input which are not tasks or commands. Still buggy as I omitted the /at command for user input.
Level-5.3: Fixed bugs. Allow both by: and at: to be displayed in the description of the task after the user types /by and /at respectively
Level-6: Fixed bugs for the delete function. Allowed an element in the list (ArrayList) to be deleted and all the subsequent elements to be pushed forward by 1
Level-6: Allows programme to exit after user types bye
